:formula_33

where formula_34 and formula_35 are the sample means of formula_6 and formula_7, and formula_38 and formula_39 are the corrected sample standard deviations of formula_6 and formula_7.

Equivalent expressions for formula_42 are
:formula_43
where formula_44 and formula_45 are the &quot;uncorrected&quot; sample standard deviations of formula_6 and formula_7.

If formula_2 and formula_49 are results of measurements that contain measurement error, the realistic limits on the correlation coefficient are not −1 to +1 but a smaller range. For the case of a linear model with a single independent variable, the coefficient of determination (R squared) is the square of formula_42, Pearson&#x27;s product-moment coefficient.

