:formula_101

which is an estimate of the covariance between variable formula_102 and variable formula_103.

The sample mean and the sample covariance matrix are unbiased estimates of the mean and the covariance matrix of the random vector formula_104, a vector whose &quot;j&quot;th element formula_105 is one of the random variables. The reason the sample covariance matrix has formula_106 in the denominator rather than formula_107 is essentially that the population mean formula_108 is not known and is replaced by the sample mean formula_109. If the population mean formula_108 is known, the analogous unbiased estimate is given by

: formula_111.

== Generalizations ==
=== Auto-covariance matrix of real random vectors ===
