where formula_4 denotes summation and formula_5 is the dimension of the vector space. For instance, in three-dimensional space, the dot product of vectors and is:
formula_6

Likewise, the dot product of the vector with itself is:
formula_7

If vectors are identified with column vectors, the dot product can also be written as a matrix product
